Welcome to the=C2=A04,534=C2=A0newly Not Boring people=C2=A0who have joined=
 us since December! If you haven=E2=80=99t subscribed, join=C2=A0181,387 sm=
art, curious folks by subscribing here:=20
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,=C2=A0
Happy Tuesday and Happy New Year! After a nice winter break and hours spent=
 staring down my Blank Page [ https://substack.com/redirect/0bf2097b-5bb6-4=
cba-ad18-52540ae9e83f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU ], we=E2=80=99re back!=C2=A0
Let=E2=80=99s kick the Not Boring new year off right: by announcing Not Bor=
ing Capital Fund III and inviting you to join in [ https://substack.com/red=
irect/f59712a8-3d05-4380-a66c-9f48bce6f0ae?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
I=E2=80=99ve been waiting to do this for a while and I can=E2=80=99t wait a=
ny longer, so let=E2=80=99s get to it.=C2=A0
Introducing Not Boring Capital Fund III
First things first, Not Boring Capital is back for Fund III: a $30 million =
fund.
I=E2=80=99ve said it before and I=E2=80=99ll say it each time: there wouldn=
=E2=80=99t be a Not Boring Capital without all of you reading and sharing a=
nd giving feedback on Not Boring, so as with Funds I & II, I flipped the sw=
itch to 506(c) in order to invite Not Boring readers to get involved.=C2=A0
$30 million Fund with a hard cap at $50 million.=C2=A0
Updated strategy more concentrated, early stage, Hard Startups, new team me=
mbers.
Early Fund III Investments in biotech, energy, education, web3, and supply =
chain alongside Lux, a16z, Thrive, Sequoia, Grelyock, 8VC, and more.
Backed by many of the same excellent LPs as Funds I & II.
Opening the Fund to accredited Not Boring readers.=C2=A0
The interest in Funds I & II blew me away. The first time we did this, for =
Fund I, 903 of you expressed $47.5 million of interest. The second time, fo=
r Fund II, 1,543 people expressed $135.6 million of interest. This is a ver=
y different market, but I=E2=80=99m nervously optimistic.=C2=A0
If you=E2=80=99d like to join us on our mission, you can submit your intere=
st here:
We want our LP group to be one of the big levers we bring to bear for our p=
ortfolio companies, so we=E2=80=99re being selective in how we put together=
 the fund. We=E2=80=99ll be prioritizing people traditionally underrepresen=
ted in LP bases, long-time Not Boring readers, investors who have participa=
ted in syndicate deals, bigger checks who want to back NBC over multiple fu=
nds, and LPs who can add insights into the categories in which we=E2=80=99r=
e investing and superpowers to our companies. I=E2=80=99ll reach out to as =
many people as we can accept ASAP.=C2=A0
A note: In case the last year hasn=E2=80=99t proven this point, let me repe=
at it: venture capital funds are risky and illiquid. Simply put: don=E2=80=
=99t invest money you=E2=80=99re not willing to lose, or to keep locked up =
for a decade. If things go well, we=E2=80=99ll be returning capital in 7-10=
 years.=C2=A0
So what=E2=80=99s new with Fund III?=C2=A0
Over the past year, I=E2=80=99ve realized that we have the opportunity to m=
ake Not Boring Capital a top tier venture fund that=E2=80=99s around for de=
cades, and to do that, we need to evolve. The core of Not Boring Capital re=
mains the same: help companies tell their stories. It=E2=80=99s just gettin=
g some upgrades.
Fund III is the harder, better, slower, stronger evolution of Not Boring Ca=
pital:
More Concentrated. We=E2=80=99re writing fewer, bigger checks, more slowly =
over a two-year period, and focusing more of our resources on each of our C=
ore investments.
Earlier Stage. We are investing Pre-Seed through Series A, where we can hav=
e the biggest impact on a company=E2=80=99s trajectory, and will look to co=
ntinue to work with breakout portfolio companies through their lives via SP=
Vs.=C2=A0
Hard Startups. We=E2=80=99re focused on Hard Startups [ https://substack.co=
m/redirect/e2e2b0ca-e7ee-47dc-bff0-4baa50d26e84?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J=
5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], the ones built on technological =
and scientific innovation, new business models, and schlep. We believe Hard=
 Startups will drive venture returns in the next decade. This isn=E2=80=99t=
 new, we=E2=80=99ve been investing in Hard Startups throughout Funds I & II=
, we=E2=80=99re just narrowing our focus.=C2=A0
Liquid Super Team. In addition to Dan [ https://substack.com/redirect/590b4=
b18-28c9-479d-a947-28c3f7ebf4f7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], who=E2=80=99s running the business side of Not B=
oring, we added two double-threats =E2=80=93 technically strong, great writ=
ers =E2=80=93 to our team in order to push out further towards the frontier=
=2E Elliot Hershberg [ https://substack.c=
